Night gradually came on.
The warm fragrance of the lavender became cooler on the wings of the light evening breeze which now arose.
From time to time a deep sigh fell on the ear as if that fearful land, consumed by ardent passions, had at length grown calm under the soft grey rain of twilight.
Abbe Mouret, hat in hand, delighted with the coolness, once more felt quietude descend upon him.
