â
Abbe Mouret drew near.
He, too, thought that he could see Albineâs orange-coloured skirt behind a juniper bush.
But Brother Archangias, in a towering passion, raised himself on tiptoe behind him, and, stretching out his fist and wagging his churlish head, thundered forth: âMay the devil take you, you brigandâs daughter!
