âPeople say what they have done when they have nothing to hide,â suddenly cried La Teuse.
And then silence reigned again.
What exasperated the old servant was the mystery the priest seemed to make about his visit to the Paradou.
She deemed herself a woman who had been shamefully deceived.
Her curiosity smarted.
She again walked round the table, not looking at the Abbe, not addressing anybody, but comforting herself with soliloquy.
âThatâs it; thatâs why we have lunch so late!
