You next, La Rousse.
Ah, well, that is splendid laurel!
You got that out of your field at Croix-Verte, I know.
â
The big girls laid their branches on the altar, which they kissed; and there they lingered for a while, handing up the greenery to La Teuse.
The sly look of devotion they had assumed on stepping on to the altar steps was quickly set aside, and soon they were laughing, digging each other with their knees, swaying their hips against the altarâs edge, and thrusting their bosoms against the tabernacle itself.
