Sergeâs languid eyes now wandered over it more freely and detected in it exquisite tints of which he had never dreamed.
It was not all blue, but rosy blue, lilac blue, tawny blue, living flesh, vast and spotless nudity heaving like a womanâs bosom in the breeze.
At every glance into space he found a fresh surprise--unknown nooks, coy smiles, bewitching rounded outlines, gauzy veils which were cast over the mighty, glorious forms of goddesses in the depths of peeping paradises.
And with his limbs lightened by suffering he winged his way amid that shimmering silk, that stainless down of azure.
