âI know, you are my love, flesh of my flesh, you are waiting for me that we may be one for ever.
I was dreaming of you.
You were in my breast, and I gave you my blood, my muscles, my bones.
I felt no pain.
You took half my heart so tenderly that I experienced keen inward delight at thus dividing myself.
I sought all that was best and most beautiful within me to give it to you.
You might have carried off everything, and still I should have thanked you.
And I woke when you went out of me.
