â
âYes,â Albine gravely declared, âit is forbidden.
All the folks of the countryside have told me that it is forbidden.
â
Then silence fell.
Serge rose from the couch where he had been lolling, and laughed, and pretended that he did not care about stories.
The sun was setting, however, before Albine would consent to go into the garden for even a few minutes.
