But as they went home, they took the path which Albine had pointed out, past the chestnuts and under the limes.
It was a path that love had consecrated.
And as they walked over the grass, they seemed to be seeking footmarks, or a fallen knot of ribbon, or a whiff of ancient perfume--something that would clearly satisfy them that they were really travelling along the path that led to the joy of union.
âWait out here,â said Albine, when they once more stood before the pavilion; âdonât come up for three minutes.
