â
âCome down at once,â implored Serge, full of alarm for her.
âI beg of you to come down.
You will be injuring yourself.
â
But she, enjoying her triumph, began to mount still higher.
She crawled along to the extreme end of a branch, grasping its leaves in her hands to maintain her hold.
âThe branch will break!
â cried Serge, thoroughly frightened.
âLet it break,â she answered, with a laugh; âit will save me the trouble of getting down.
â
And the branch did break, but only slowly, with such deliberation that, as it gradually settled towards the ground, it let Albine slip down in very gentle fashion.
