You shaânât get it, you shaânât get it!
â
And then she sprang forward; but Serge, thanks to his long legs, outstripped her and plucked the poppy, which he waved about victoriously.
She stood there with lips compressed, saying nothing, but feeling a strong inclination to cry.
Serge threw down the flower.
Nothing else occurred to him.
Then, to make his peace with her, he asked: âWould you like me to carry you as I did the other day?
