She had gathered up her petticoats and fastened them together with a piece of string.
And she advanced quietly into the water, taking the greatest care not to disturb it.
When she was quite close to some tiny fish, that lay lurking between a couple of pebbles, she thrust down her bare arm, made a wild grasp, and brought her hand up again with nothing in it but sand and gravel.
