He could distinctly hear the stir of the village life.
Those peasants, those women and children, he knew them.
There was the mayor, Bambousse, returning from Les Olivettes, calculating how much the approaching vintage would yield him; there were the Brichets, the husband crawling along, and the wife moaning with misery.
