There had been no regular wedding-feast; but, in the evening, after dinner, a ten-gallon âDame Janeâ had been placed upon the table, and they were making it their business to empty it before going to bed.
There were ten of them, and old Bambousse was already with one hand tilting over the jar whence only a thread of red liquor now flowed.
