â She still had her apron full of herbage with her, and her pets were taking it by assault.
A troop of fowls had surrounded her, clucking and calling each other, and pecking at the hanging green stuff.
The goat pushed its head slyly under her arm, and began to eat the longer leaves.
Even the cow, which was tethered to the wall, strained at its cord and poked out its nose, kissing her with its warm breath.
âOh!
