The ascent of Calvary is very tiring.
He has dropped down on His knees.
But He does not stay to wipe even the sweat from His brow, He rises up again and continues His journey.... And again Jesus falls beneath the weight of His cross.
At each step He staggers.
This time He has fallen on His side, so heavily that for a moment He lies there quite breathless.
His lacerated hands have relaxed their hold upon the cross.
His bruised and aching feet leave blood-stained prints behind them.
