He played his card, which La Teuse took with a knave.
Then he threw himself back in his chair and again burst into one of his loud laughs.
He did not seem to be able to work himself up into a genuine rage that evening.
âWell, well,â he grumbled, ânever mind, even if she did see him, she had a smacking fall on her nose.
