It was raining, you know.
I was standing by the school-door when I caught sight of her coming down from the church.
She was walking along quite straight and upright, in her stuck-up fashion, in spite of the pouring rain.
But when she got into the road, she tumbled down full length, no doubt because the ground was so slippery.
Oh!
how I did laugh!
How I did laugh!
I clapped my hands, too.
When she picked herself up again, I saw she was bleeding at the wrist.
I shall feel happy over it for a week.
I cannot think of her lying there on the ground without feeling the greatest delight.
